  <folder>
    <_title>Other Maemo Weather</_title>
    <topic>
      <_topictitle>Introduction</_topictitle>
      <context contextUID="help_omweather_intro"/>
      <_para>Welcome to Other Maemo Weather.</_para>
      <_para>
        Other Maemo Weather (OMWeather) is a weather applet for Nokia Internet
	Tablets. It can be used to:
      </_para>
      <list>
        <_listitem>
          Check detailed weather forecast for up to 10 days
        </_listitem>
        <_listitem>
          Update weather information automatically from the Internet (Data
	  provided by weather.com)
        </_listitem>
        <_listitem>
          Configure nearest weather station automatically using GPS
        </_listitem>
        <_listitem>
          Easily to select custom weather station from the sorted drop down menu
        </_listitem>
        <_listitem>
          See sunrise and sunset times for selected weather stations
        </_listitem>
        <_listitem>
          See current phase of the moon
        </_listitem>
        <_listitem>
          Select between different icon sizes, icon sets, colors and view modes
        </_listitem>
        <_listitem>
          See some eye candy with transparency option
        </_listitem>
       </list>
      <_para>
        Use the <ref refid="help_omweather_" refdoc="index"/> to use the
        various sections of this help document.
      </_para>
    </topic>
    <topic>
      <_topictitle>Getting Started</_topictitle>
      <context contextUID="help_omweather_getstarted"/>
      <_para>
        To activate OMWeather select <display_text>Home</display_text> 
        <display_text>Select applets...</display_text>
        <display_text>OMWeather</display_text>.
      </_para>
      <_para>
        First thing to do is select the position of a OMWeather applet in home
	view. You can change applet's position simply touching it and dragging
	it where you want it. Appearance of the applet can be changed from the
	<display_text>Tool</display_text> icon in OMWeathers weather window or
	selecting <display_text>Home</display_text>
	<display_text>Applet settings</display_text>
        <display_text>OMWeather settings</display_text>.
      </_para>
      <_para>
        OMWeather will use the tablet's home city selection as a default location
        for weather data. Location can be changed from the
	<display_text>Stations</display_text> tab in OMWeathers	settings window.
      </_para>
      <_para>
	More info about how to change appearance of the applet and add, rename and
	delete locations can be	found on the 
	<ref refid="help_omweather_settings" refdoc="Settings"/> page.
      </_para>
    </topic>
    <topic>
      <_topictitle>Settings</_topictitle>
      <context contextUID="help_omweather_settings"/>
      <_para>
        The <display_text>Settings</display_text> dialog (accessible from
        the desktop applet or home view's applet settings menu) provides
        access to the configurable options that controls how OMWeather
        appears and run. In addition to the tabs, there are also four
	buttons. Left arrow will take you to weather view, ok button saves settings,
	question mark opens help and x button closes settings window.
      </_para>
      <_para>
        <display_text>Stations</display_text> tab lists all locations 
        which weather data OMWeather will receive when the applet's refresh button
	is touched or automatic update happens.
      </_para>
      <_para>
        <display_text>Visuals</display_text> tab is used to configure 
        settings that controls visual appearance of the OMWeather.
      </_para>
      <_para>
        <display_text>Display</display_text> tab is used to configure 
        settings that control the number of visible items, its size and
	some other parameters of the OMWeather.
      </_para>
      <_para>
        <display_text>Units</display_text> tab is used to select temperature,
        distance, wind speed and pressure units shown on weather data.  Necessary units can
	be selected by clicking on corresponding check button.
      </_para>
      <_para>
        <display_text>Update</display_text> tab is used to configure 
        update interval of a weather data.  This tab shows also time
	when next update will be done. 
      </_para>
      <_para>
	<display_text>Sensor</display_text> tab is used control if temperature from
	the internal sensor is shown on the applet.
      </_para>
    </topic>
    <topic>
      <_topictitle>Settings. Stations tab</_topictitle>
      <context contextUID="help_omweather_settings_stations"/>
	<_para>
        Left section allows you to rename and remove
	stations in the list. <display_text>Up</display_text> and
	<display_text>down</display_text> arrows allow you to change the
	order of the selected locations.
      </_para>
      <_para>
        Right (<display_text>Add</display_text>) section allows you to add new
        weather stations, which will then be listed in the left view.
      </_para>
      <_para>
        <display_text>Enable GPS:</display_text> check box is used to
	enable automatic weather station selection if GPS is enabled. 
	This option works only for OS2008.
      </_para>
    </topic>
    <topic>
      <_topictitle>Settings. Visuals tab</_topictitle>
      <context contextUID="help_omweather_settings_visuals"/>
      <_para>
        <display_text>Visuals</display_text> tab is used to configure 
        settings that control the visual appearance of the OMWeather.
      </_para>
      <_para>
        <display_text>Layout:</display_text> selects how icons are shown on
	the home screen.  Possible selections are one row, one column, two
	rows, two columns or combination.
      </_para>
      <_para>
        <display_text>Icon set:</display_text> selects which icon set is used.
	You can install more icon sets with the application manager (if Maemo
	extras repository is configured) or going to OMWeathers Maemo garage
	page (http://omweather.garage.maemo.org/) and downloading icon sets
	directly from there.
      </_para>
      <_para>
        <display_text>UI Theme Override</display_text> selection allows to override
	theme settings.
      </_para>
      <_para>
	<display_text>Transparency:</display_text> selection for OS2006-OS2007 will show
	background image behind the icons. For OS2008 this option allows to select the percentage
	for semi-transparency.
      </_para>
      <_para>
	<display_text>Font:</display_text> defines font and it's size used
	by applet on the tablet home screen.
      </_para>
      <_para>
	<display_text>Font color:</display_text> defines applet's font color.
	Touching color button will open
	<display_text>Pick a Color</display_text> dialog where it's possible to
	select font color.
      </_para>
      <_para>
	<display_text>Background color:</display_text> setting defines the
	background color used for icons. For OS2006-OS2007 background color is not
	selectable if transparency is used.
      </_para>
    </topic>
    <topic>
      <_topictitle>Settings. Display tab</_topictitle>
      <context contextUID="help_omweather_settings_display"/>
      <_para>
        <display_text>Display</display_text> tab is used to configure 
        settings that control the number of visible items, it's size and
	some other parameters of OMWeather.
      </_para>
      <_para>
        <display_text>Visible items:</display_text> selects how many icons
        will be shown in the tablet's home screen.
      </_para>
      <_para>
	<display_text>Icon size:</display_text> defines icon size.
      </_para>
      <_para>
	<display_text>Show only current weather on first icon</display_text>
	selection will show current weather on first icon and forecast for the
	rest of the day is shown on the next icon.
      </_para>
      <_para>
	<display_text>Swap hi/low temperature</display_text> selection will
	change way how lowest and highest temperature for a day is shown on the
	applet.	If selected, applet will show high temperature first.	
      </_para>
      <_para>
	<display_text>Show wind</display_text> selection will show wind
	speed and direction on the applet.
      </_para>
      <_para>
	<display_text>Show station name:</display_text> selection will
	control if station names are shown on the applet.
      </_para>
      <_para>
	<display_text>Show arrows:</display_text> selection will
	control if arrows used to change weather station are shown on the
	applet.
      </_para>
    </topic>
    <topic>
      <_topictitle>Settings. Units tab</_topictitle>
      <context contextUID="help_omweather_settings_units"/>
      <_para>
        <display_text>Units</display_text> tab is used to select temperature,
        distance, wind speed and pressure units shown on weather data.
	Necessary units can be selected by clicking on corresponding check button.
      </_para>
    </topic>
    <topic>
      <_topictitle>Settings. Update tab</_topictitle>
      <context contextUID="help_omweather_settings_update"/>
      <_para>
        <display_text>Update</display_text> tab is used to configure 
        update interval of a weather data.  This tab shows also time
	when next update will be done. 
      </_para>
      <_para>
	<display_text>Automatically updating data when connecting to the Internet:
	</display_text> selection controls automatic weather data update when
	Internet connection is established.
      </_para>
      <_para>
	<display_text>Switch to the next station after:</display_text> drop down
	menu controls time after applet changes to next weather station.
      </_para>
      <_para>
	Valid time for current weather and update interval can be selected from
	a drop down menu. 
      </_para>
    </topic>
    <topic>
      <_topictitle>Settings. Sensor tab</_topictitle>
      <context contextUID="help_omweather_settings_sensor"/>
      <_para>
	<display_text>Sensor</display_text> tab is used control if temperature from
	the internal sensor is shown on the applet.
      </_para>
      <_para>
	When <display_text>Use device temperature sensor</display_text> check
	box is enabled, applet will show the temperature of the built-in temperature
	sensor. Temperature can be shown after station name or on a new icon.
	Sensor read interval can be set by user from 1-30 minutes.
      </_para>
    </topic>
    <topic>
      <_topictitle>Using Desktop Applet</_topictitle>
      <context contextUID="help_omweather_usingdesktopapplet"/>
      <_para>
        Touching icon of a day brings up a window where you can see
	current weather or detailed forecast for a selected day.
	On the <display_text>Now</display_text> tab you can see current
	weather and phase of the moon.  <display_text>Day</display_text>
	tabs will show weather forecast	and sunrise/sunset times for a
	selected days. 
      </_para>
      <_para>
	<display_text>Tool</display_text> button will open OMWeather
	settings dialog.  <display_text>Refresh</display_text> button will
	update weather data, <display_text>Question mark</display_text>
	will open OMWeather info and <display_text>X</display_text> button
	closes weather dialog.
      </_para>
    </topic>
